    "These AI-driven tools would enable a comprehensive, interactive, and accessible educational experience, benefiting both students and educators.",
    "Figure 2 depicts the generative AI workflow process and its potential applications in orthopedic education, demonstrating how these technologies could aid in providing engaging, adaptable, and effective learning experiences.",
    "Learning methodologiesLLMs, such as GPT-4 and Gemini, can help improve orthopedic education programs by supplementing lecture content with real-time explanations, additional resources, and background information.",
    "While, students can get this information by searching Google [58], using point-of-care resources, or mobile applications [59], generative AI distinguishes itself by providing knowledge in a concise, practical, and understandable format.",
    "Generative AI can also be used to promote small-group discussions by asking thought-provoking queries, encouraging conversations between peers, and establishing an interesting and collaborative learning atmosphere [60]."
